        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Xinzuo PM8O Zhen Series</strong> combines 67-layer Damascus steel with olive wood and black buffalo horn handles for a blade that commands attention. The 10Cr15CoMoV core at HRC 60 provides reliable edge retention, while the premium handle materials give each knife a distinctive, natural character. This series stands out for its wide selection of specialty knives — including the honesuki (Japanese boning knife) and sakimaru — alongside essential kitchen blades from paring to 10-inch carving. The buffalo horn bolster adds visual contrast and serves as a natural moisture barrier between blade and handle. For cooks who appreciate premium materials and want access to specialty Japanese knife types, the PM8O Zhen Series is a compelling choice.</p>",
